{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "Enjoying the sport and all the new people you meet. Advice is to give anything you're even remotely interested in a go."}

{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Warwick is a really great place to meet people and have a valuable university experience. Keep in mind it is a campus uni and therefore can get a little claustrophobic.'}

{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'I am really enjoying Warwick. My advice is to make the most of all the unique learning facilities such as the learning grid. Also, take advantage of facilities such as the arts centre, and have a fab time like me!'}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'The learning grid should be 24 hours. There should be shuttle bus to Cannon Park. Need more SU events!'}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Pretty good. Be open minded and just have fun!'}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Make sure you pick a course that you think you will enjoy and do some research before deciding on which uni you choose.'}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "Good campus. It's green with lots of facilities. Warwick business school is also ranked very well."}

column3: Instrumental and Analytical Methods in Biological and Environmental Chemistry PgDip
column4: {'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'My subject course is interesting, my opportunities to get involved with clubs and societies are plentiful, and the tutors are helpful.'}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "It's a great experience although I don't enjoy my course massively. Great university and accomodation though."}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "The university's outside accomodation is OK. However, the bus service is not good so should be improved. "}

column3: Economics, Politics and International Studies BA (Hons)
column4: {'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Uni has been great so far, the lectures have been brilliant, campus is great and the people are all lovely. A piece of advice would be to manage your time well, and try to get involved with as much as possible whilst at uni with societies events because time is limited!'}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'The SU is awesome but the facilities need to be improved a little bit. Also, costcutter is way too expensive.'}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "It's been quite enjoyable. One important piece of advice would be to be open and confident. "}

{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "Everything is good on paper; facilities, library and buildings are all good. The main problem is the other people at Warwick. They don't have much of a sense of humour. Definitely recommend if you want to do maths but didn’t get into Cambridge."}

{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "The SU is far too commercialised. It's also too expensive to join clubs, sports and societies. The Uni should subsidise extra-curricular activities to allow more people to be involved."}

column3: Economics, Politics and International Studies BA (Hons)
column4: {'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Start working from the very start, and join as many societies as you can during first year!'}

{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "Warwick's a nice campus uni to hang out in and around. You always run into people you know which is good. My course is fine, and im enjoying being part of sports/societies. The facilities at Warwick are really good, especially sports facilities. Costcutter could be a little bit cheaper, but that's the only thing really. Reccommend."}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "It's pretty good for most things, however it can be boring on the weekends. Advice would be to make the most of extra curricular stuff."}

{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "The uni is awful, full of stuck-up snobs. Don't take discrete maths, no departments care about you. Not good for joint degrees. You may get a good job at the end of it, but I'm having the worst 3 years of my life. Nightlife is bad, everyone focusses on getting drunk."}

{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Best economics course in the UK. Heronbank is a nice accomodation, although quiet at times. Kasbah is good in Coventry, and Gatecrasher is good in Birmingham, but leamington clubs get boring. University facilities are excellent, such as sport facilities and the learning grid. There is a huge selection of societies and clubs. There are good places to eat, and the dirty duck is a nice pub.'}

{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Stay in Rootes, it is easily the most fun. Use the learning grid sometimes. Join socieites and get to know as many people as possible. Warwick is fun!'}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Great campus and a very good economics department. Having a great time.'}

column3: International Cultural Policy and Management MA
column4: {'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'To be honest, there are many crimes in the post grad hub. (PC stolen, wallet stolen, keys stolen…). There was also a car accident in which a student was killed. Coventry is horrible, but being within a nice calm countryside is the best environment for studying.'}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "Go out lots, don't forget that first year doesn't count! I couldn't have asked for a better first six months. "}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "Warwick's been great so far. Make sure you join a sports club or a society to really make the most of the social life."}

{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "The SU is great, until you become an exec member of a sport or society and realise they are super unhelpful. No-one can say that Warwick doesn't have a society for everyone (LARP?). Choose your course carefully. It's better to do something you actually enjoy rather than something you believe will lead you straight into a job, the chances are it probably wont. Get involved as much as you can... most people see their degree as secondary anyway. Finally, never try and do all the reading... you never, ever, EVER will."}

{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'The university is good but my course is not exctly what I expected. The lectures are ok, but extra activities could be done to ensure adequate learning.'}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Overall good, but campus is too big and so better on-campus travelling provisions are required.'}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'I love Warwick, but the union nightlife desperately needs improving. More variation and consistent events.'}

{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Yes, enjoying the university experience. A great experience and a different environment. Those who are looking forward to coming here will have a great time but be prepared for the cold!'}

column3: International Cultural Policy and Management MA
column4: {'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'If you are looking for a place only to study, then this is the place. Campus life is quiet and don’t expect to have a social life unless you are here for drinks.'}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Great experience. Great opportunity to meet new people and have fun. Enjoy first year but make sure to work hard too. '}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Great flatmates! Course is interesting and nightlife is pretty decent.'}

{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'The reputation of Warwick resonates well with employers and will help you get a job. The accomodation is affordable and not bad for what you get (good size). However there is no city life (campus uni).'}

{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "The course is interesting but can be irrelevant and longer than needed. Living in leamington is better than living on campus, and the clubs in leamington are good. However the SU doesn't have much to do."}

{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Warwick campus has great facilities and a wide range of events and activities. Staff are usually helpful and well informed, and lectures are well organised.'}

column3: Instrumental and Analytical Methods in Biological and Environmental Chemistry PgDip
column4: {'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'The university is pretty good. However, need more clubs in Leamington to improve the nightlife.'}

{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': '1. tutors are useful 2. Rootes is cheap and cleaner comes often 3. Leamington is lovely 4. Great gym 5. Lots of societies to choose from 6. in terms of eye candy, the guys are kind of short.'}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Make the most out of socialising in first year! Make sure not to get too bogged down with work.'}

{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "1. It's awesome! Make sure you take advantage of all the clubs and societies! 2. don't waste your money on booze 3. go to the arts centre as much as possible. Everything I've been to see has been amazing and cheap for students. 4. get the work/play balance right. 5 visit your tutors. annoy them and get your money's worth!"}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "Join loads of societies when you arrive. It's when you'll have the most time to make the most of these."}

{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'My course is un-interesting and not immersing with not enough time spent in smaller groups. The uni has a good night-life with Leamington and Coventry close by. There is a good chance of getting a job, even if I have learned nothing.'}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "Nothing like I've experienced before! Very difficult course but nothing that I didn't expect. Overall very happy!"}

{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Warwick has been amazing. It has provided great opportunities for networking, and career opportunities. My course has been fantastic and I would highly recommend the university overall.'}

{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "Uni life is great, it gives you an opportunity to be independent but also to have loads of fun! Piece of advice. Join loads of societies, have fun and remember that first year doesn't count towards your final degree!"}

column3: International Cultural Policy and Management MA
column4: {'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'I feel that the bus services could be improved. They could be more accessible, and also cheaper. Other than that the University is ok.'}

{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'The law part is quite difficult to understand, should have more support from the university to let students receive better knowledge. Business is relatively easier, so far so good. '}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Warwick is nice. The campus is good and has a good SU; all facilities are close by. '}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Warwick is alright. Good courses and lectures, and lots of extra curricular activities to get involved in.'}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'The uni is really good, excellent staff. Lectures could be better scheduled (no gaps!)'}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Advice would be to record lectures. Method of ensuring cleanliness of kitchen could be changed. Love societies.'}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'The campus and the people here are both lovely. The facilities are great although I do think costcutter should be cheaper.'}

{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "I'm having a really fantastic time with plenty of wonderful new people, experiences and knowledge. I recommend being as open and social as you're comfortable with, seizing every opportunity available and having a great time. "}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "Good for engineering because of investments. However, I wouldn't want to be a humanities student."}

{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "Warwick is really good for educational value but not too good for eye candy. To be honest, we live in a bit of a bubble where ugly people are seen as 'hot'. A Warwick 8 is a real life 4. Depressing."}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Warwick has a huge variety of societies that you can get involved in, so it’s a nice place to develop your skills.'}

{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "I've enjoyed pretty much me entire time at Warwick. Make sure to get involved with as many sports and societies as you can. The facilities are good, including the new gym. Also, accomodation is pretty good aswell but make sure you choose it wisely. Some are definitely quieter than others. If you want a more fun halls, go with rootes."}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "Make sure you choose the right course! Make an effort to mix and socialise during freshers or you'll regret it."}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Enjoying the course and have met some great people. Would advise students to join as many clubs as possible and meet loads of people.'}

column3: Evidence-Based Musculoskeletal Care (Managing Upper Limb Pain) PGA
column4: {'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'The course is great as you get a lot of freedom to take modules of your choice. In your 2nd and 3rd year social life revolves around sports clubs and societies, so get involved. The nights out are decent to start with but going to the same few places eventually gets abit boring. Overall though, Warwick is a great uni, and its graduates are looked upon very highly be employers.'}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Get involved in the huge range of clubs and socities. The whole experience is amazing with so many things to do on and off campus.'}

{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Very different to school, but I feel the courses are poor value for money. Great facilities though, and an excellent seminar system that works well with independent learning.'}

{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "Loving Warwick so far. In my final year and it's been great. Course is good and have loved playing sports. My advice would be to make the most of every opportunity you get."}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Good campus university but be prepared for no city life. Career prospects appear to be good and lecturers are always focussed. '}

column3: Instrumental and Analytical Methods in Biological and Environmental Chemistry PgDip
column4: {'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Advice: get involved with as much as possible and make sure you have a good work and social life balance!'}

{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "I'm really enjoying my uni experience. Everybody is friendly, there is plenty to do and lots of places to go out. Overall, it is a really nice place to study."}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "I'd recommend rootes halls. They're the most fun. Top Uni though. Although the SU needs better performers."}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Enjoying the university. Few problems, but am definitely still glad I came here. '}

column3: Economics, Politics and International Studies BA (Hons)
column4: {'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Consider other factors other than university ranking when choosing university.'}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Good experience and good facilities. However it should be more lively.'}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "Good. However, don't come for the student life if you are a Masters student."}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Been pretty good banter so far. Everything pretty near and people seem nice.'}

{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "Warwick was my first choice uni and I'm so glad I got in. The facilities are brilliant, the staff helpful and the students friendly. Highly recommended."}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'University has been good. However, the courses could be more challenging for first years.'}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'We definitely need more accomodation for students! More choice and more campus rooms in general.'}

{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'As far as accommodation in first year goes, pick rootes if you want the opportunity for lots of nights out. Other accommodations don’t embrace it in the same way.'}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "Amazeballs! Unity in diversity. Don't cause a ruckus at Heronbank."}

{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'I really enjoy the social aspect of Warwick and have made good friends in my accomodation and course. Loads of work though and accomodation could be refurbished.'}

column3: Evidence-Based Musculoskeletal Care (Managing Upper Limb Pain) PGA
column4: {'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Most convenient of all other universities, especially the ones in London. Lower cost so you save more!'}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "Be careful when applying to Warwick. I love my course but we're in the middle of nowhere and it's most definitely a disadvantage."}

column3: Evidence-Based Musculoskeletal Care (Managing Upper Limb Pain) PGA
column4: {'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "I'm really enjoying Warwick at the moment, as I have the opportunity to work and have fun at the same time. Advice is to do as many things as you can in first year."}

{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "You need to get used to living on campus, and being 15 minutes away from Coventry city centre. People are friendly here and the courses are great. It's a great place for study."}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Having a good time but the clubs could be better.'}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "If you can find a better campus based university, you're either at Oxbridge, or you're out of the country."}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Be prepared to be balanced between working hard and having fun. I guess that is what university life is about.'}

{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Heard from a teacher how good Warwick is, but I had no idea how good. Aside from excellent academic prospects and how employable a degree from here is, the social life is amazing and you are welcome pretty much anywhere in terms of sports and societies.'}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "It's good, pretty fun in general. There are loads of opportunities to meet cool people."}

{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Very good academically and job prospects. However there is a bubble lifestyle with no big clubs but that is sometimes nice because you always end up bumping into a bunch of people you know.'}

{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'The seclusion of the campus can mean that living on campus can be a little like living in a bubble. I would recommend trying to experience nearby towns and off campus life/nightlife as much as possible.'}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Campus is great and everyone is really friendly. The only thing that could be better is the catering on campus.'}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'You wont regret applying to Warwick, the quality of the course and the sense of community makes it an enbeatable place to be.'}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'I love the SU, but campus life might get boring after a while.'}

{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "Great. Make sure you look at all aspects. My course is different to what I thought but still great! Don't worry about lectures, they're all good!"}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'No.1 Recommendation: live in Rootes! Westwood, Sherbourne and Heronbank are too far from campus.'}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Warwick is nice enough. Could be better, could be worse. Advice would be to choose your course wisely.'}

{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': "Warwick is a nice uni. Lots to do, and lots of cool people. Pick your course wisely (do research). The nightlife is ok but can get samey. The SU is also ok, but only if you go on the right occassions. Overall I've enjoyed Warwick, and would recommend it to others. Good all round!"}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'I am enjoying uni life. I would advise those coming to uni or college to investigate what the course actually entails before coming.'}
{'Tell us about your overall university experience so far.': 'Warwick allowed a great balance between quality teaching, career preparation and extra curricular fun (sports) '}
column5: {'How does your uni make efforts to increase your employability (careers department, work placements, transferable skills)?': 'Excellent progression onto top graduate programs'}
column10: {"What do you think of your Students' Union in terms of student representation and facilities?": "This was refurbished while I was there, it was much larger but it has lost some its charm. Gigs were pretty poor although DJ's improved ..."}
column11: {'What do you think about the safety, condition, location and cost of your accommodation?': 'Good - variety of facilities'}
column12: {'Is your university in a good location in terms of distance to accommodation and local amenities?': 'Close to Coventry, which I visited once. I spent most of the time in Leam or on campus.'}
column13: {'How would you rate the variety of societies/sports?': "I was a member of the football club, this was a superb experience and I'm still in touch with many of the people in the teams.
